HEADWORD: Deadlatch
<hw>Dead"latch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of latch
whose bolt may be so locked by a detent that it can not be opened from
the inside by the handle, or from the outside by the latch key.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

